-- FTSE 100 Index Pares Losses After Fed's Bernanke Indicates More Stimulus
-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 2010-10-15T12:20:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/u-k-stocks-pare-losses-after-bernanke-indicates-more-stimulus-by-the-fed.html
U.K. stocks recouped losses after
Federal Reserve Chairman Ben S. Bernanke said additional
monetary stimulus may be warranted because inflation is too low
and unemployment is too high.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index was little changed at 5,724.81
as of 1:19 p.m. in London, having earlier fallen as much as 0.5
percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Adam Haigh at 
 ahaigh1@bloomberg.net  